	   <tr><td colspan=2>Was camping the orc miner spawn at the entrance.  First spawn you come to.  Bout a 20 minute spawn was just about to hit camp and figured what the hell will talk for a little bit.  Talked for about 15 mins and said what the hell will get one more spawn.  BOOM Herbist.  Think wow I could really use the bag.  This drops.  I ALMOST sold this to some gnome that said he would give me 1kp for this.  Figured I would look it up first before selling it.  Didnt even think about what it might be worth.  Am really glad I didn't.  Sounds like I can get much more the 1kp for it.<br><br>Herbist was blue to a 35 Ranger.  Pretty easy kill.  He dispells though so be carefull.  Would have been an easy fight excpet he dispelled my Barbcoat (2pt damage sheild with some AC) at the start.  In a normal fight I get about 100 to 200 points of damage out of the sheild.  Ended up with around bubble and a half hps from just over 1.1khps and half mana.  Had to root him and cast a few heals though.  Just run around a corner and you can rest without fear of him casting on you.<br>He also will root you, which can be really bad.  If he is wandering around make sure you can finish him off in a hurry when he starts getting low or he will gate on you to his bind point heal and come back for more with some friends to help him.  He casted some kind of ice DD spell.  He also casts Tagor's on you which can be deadly.  Would have killed me if he got it to stick.  He will try to cast it in the beggining of the fight.  He only tried it once on me. <br><br>Would be really easy fight for 2 of just about any class combo.  Can be soloed at 35 if you play it right.<br><br>Also drops Crystal Shroud (robe pretty good stats), and Herbist Pack/Bag whatever.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
